      "description": "Available is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the iconic S54 3.2L naturally aspirated inline-six engine. This unit delivers 333 hp through six individual throttle bodies and a Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox. The chassis has been enhanced with a reinforced rear subframe and Powerflex bushings to address common E46 floor pan fatigue. Recent mechanical service includes a comprehensive Double VANOS overhaul and a precision valve adjustment, ensuring the high-revving valvetrain is optimized for its 8,000 RPM redline. Power is managed by the M Variable Differential Lock, providing exceptional lateral grip and corner-exit traction. This is a mechanically sorted example with a linear power band and a taut, responsive suspension geometry, ideal for the spirited driver.",
